Americanized form of Swiss German <b>Künzi</b> (see   Kuenzi  ).","History: The paternal grandfather of NJ and PA legislator John Kinsey (1693–1750) was one of the commissioners sent out from England in 1677 by the West Jersey proprietors to buy land from the Indians and to lay out a town. John was the leader of the Quaker party in the PA assembly and chief justice of the PA supreme court."]},{"name":"McKenzie","meanings":["Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Coinnich</b>, a patronymic from the personal name <i>Coinneach</i> meaning ‘comely’, Anglicized as <i>Kenneth</i>. Compare the Irish form   McKinney   2. The Scottish spelling with <i>-z-</i> indicates palatalization of the <i>-n-</i> (compare   Menzies  ).","History: This is the name of a Scottish Highland clan, historically associated with the mountainous district of Kintail in nortwestern Scotland, with Cromarty, and with Loch Seaforth (Loch Shiphoirt) on the Island of Harris."]}]},{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes MacKenzie was born in 1440, in Craighall, Perthshire, Scotland. She married Roderick MacLeod 7th of Lewes before 1458, in Scotland. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 1 daughter. She died in 1481, in Assynt, Sutherland, Scotland, at the age of 41, and was buried in Assynt, Sutherland, Scotland."},"et":{"1440–1481":"1440–1481","1420–1598":"1420–1598","1458–1511":"1458–1511","1462–Female":"1462–Surnud","1490–1520":"1490–1520","1528–1560":"1528–1560","before 1458":"enne 1458","1440":"1440","1462":"1462","1560":"1560","1481":"1481","1490":"1490","1458":"1458","1511":"1511","1598":"1598","1520":"1520","1420":"1420","about 1462":"umbes 1462","1528":"1528","Isle of Lewis, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Isle of Lewis, Ross-shire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Assynt, Sutherland, Scotland":"Assynt, Sutherland, Scotland","Craighall, Perthshire, Scotland":"Craighall, Perthshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1440–1481":"1440–1481","1420–1598":"1420–1598","1458–1511":"1458–1511","1462–Female":"1462–Kuollut","1490–1520":"1490–1520","1528–1560":"1528–1560","before 1458":"ennen vuotta 1458","1440":"1440","1462":"1462","1560":"1560","1481":"1481","1490":"1490","1458":"1458","1511":"1511","1598":"1598","1520":"1520","1420":"1420","about 1462":"noin 1462","1528":"1528","Isle of Lewis, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Isle of Lewis, Ross-shire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Assynt, Sutherland, Scotland":"Assynt, Sutherland, Scotland","Craighall, Perthshire, Scotland":"Craighall, Perthshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1440–1481":"1440–1481","1420–1598":"1420–1598","1458–1511":"1458–1511","1462–Female":"1462–Décédée","1490–1520":"1490–1520","1528–1560":"1528–1560","before 1458":"avant 1458","1440":"1440","1462":"1462","1560":"1560","1481":"1481","1490":"1490","1458":"1458","1511":"1511","1598":"1598","1520":"1520","1420":"1420","about 1462":"environ 1462","1528":"1528","Isle of Lewis, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Isle of Lewis, Ross-shire, Écosse","Scotland":"Écosse","Assynt, Sutherland, Scotland":"Assynt, Sutherland, Écosse","Craighall, Perthshire, Scotland":"Craighall, Perthshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Agnes MacKenzie est née en 1440, à Craighall, Perthshire, Écosse. Elle a épousé Roderick MacLeod 7th of Lewes avant 1458, à Écosse. Ils ont eu au moins 3 fils et 1 fille. Elle est décédée en 1481, à Assynt, Sutherland, Écosse, à l’âge de 41 ans, et a été enterrée à Assynt, Sutherland, Écosse."},"de":{"1440–1481":"1440–1481","1420–1598":"1420–1598","1458–1511":"1458–1511","1462–Female":"1462–Verstorben","1490–1520":"1490–1520","1528–1560":"1528–1560","before 1458":"vor 1458","1440":"1440","1462":"1462","1560":"1560","1481":"1481","1490":"1490","1458":"1458","1511":"1511","1598":"1598","1520":"1520","1420":"1420","about 1462":"um 1462","1528":"1528","Isle of Lewis, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Isle of Lewis, Ross-shire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Assynt, Sutherland, Scotland":"Assynt, Sutherland, Scotland","Craighall, Perthshire, Scotland":"Craighall, Perthshire, Scotland","lifeSummary":"Agnes MacKenzie wurde 1440 in Craighall, Perthshire, Scotland geboren. Sie hat vor 1458 in Scotland Roderick MacLeod 7th of Lewes geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 3 Söhne und 1 Tochter. Sie starb 1481 im Alter von 41 Jahren in Assynt, Sutherland, Scotland und wurde in Assynt, Sutherland, Scotland begraben."},"ht":{"1440–1481":"1440–1481","1420–1598":"1420–1598","1458–1511":"1458–1511","1462–Female":"1462–Desede","1490–1520":"1490–1520","1528–1560":"1528–1560","before 1458":"before 1458","1440":"1440","1462":"1462","1560":"1560","1481":"1481","1490":"1490","1458":"1458","1511":"1511","1598":"1598","1520":"1520","1420":"1420","about 1462":"about 1462","1528":"1528","Isle of Lewis, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Isle of Lewis, Ross-shire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Assynt, Sutherland, Scotland":"Assynt, Sutherland, Scotland","Craighall, Perthshire, Scotland":"Craighall, Perthshire, Scotland"},"hu":{"1440–1481":"1440–1481","1420–1598":"1420–1598","1458–1511":"1458–1511","1462–Female":"1462–elhunyt","1490–1520":"1490–1520","1528–1560":"1528–1560","before 1458":"1458 előtt","1440":"1440","1462":"1462","1560":"1560","1481":"1481","1490":"1490","145